    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A variant of the carbon process to produce contact prints; the image is formed from a pigment, usually carbon black, in a colloid suspension that has been made light-sensitive with bichromates. Marketed under the name Charbon Velours.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Variante de la carbotipia para producir copias de contacto. La imagen se forma con un pigmento, normalmente negro de carbón, en una suspensión coloidal que ha sido convertida en fotosensible con bicromatos. Comercializada bajo el nombre Charbon Velours (Terciopelos de carbón).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Variant van de kooldruk voor het maken van contactafdrukken. Het beeld wordt gevormd uit pigment, meestal carbonzwart, in een colloïdesuspensie die lichtgevoelig is gemaakt met behulp van bichromaten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052399/Nederlandse Film en televisieacademie</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種碳粉印相法，在膠質感光材料尚未乾透時，由碳墨等色料形成影像，製出的成品其中一面為感光面並直接接觸底片；所用相紙在市場上以「絨碳」（Charbon Velours）為名。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
